title: DR 2023
name: DR (2023)
synopsis: Ruined, the 2023 American psychological thriller, directed by Tamara Bass and penned by Michelle Valentine, delves into a web of suspense and betrayal. With a cast featuring Keri Hilson, Tami Roman, and Wendy Raquel Robinson, the film immerses viewers in a story where trust becomes a precious commodity and revenge fuels a sinister agenda. At its core, Ruined follows the journey of a woman grappling to salvage her marriage. Seeking counseling as a lifeline, she unwittingly steps into a labyrinth of deceit. Her therapist, harboring a secret past with her husband, harbors a chilling thirst for revenge. As the plot unfolds, the boundaries between ally and adversary blur, and survival becomes a matter of wits and resilience. Premiering on BET+ on August 25, 2023, Ruined has sparked conversations among critics and audiences alike. The film's reception, while mixed, highlights its strengths in performances and a suspense-laden atmosphere. Yet, critiques emerge concerning plot coherence and character depth. The film's official synopsis offers a tantalizing glimpse into the narrative's intricacies. Against a backdrop of psychological tension, the story navigates the treacherous terrain of trust and deception. As alliances unravel and motives intertwine, the question of survival looms ominously. Keri Hilson takes on the role of the woman grappling with her marriage's fate, while Tami Roman embodies the enigmatic therapist with a hidden agenda. Wendy Raquel Robinson adds another layer of intrigue as the woman's confidante. The ensemble cast includes Sean Ringgold, Michael Jai White, and Vanessa Bell Calloway, further enriching the film's dynamics. With a runtime of 90 minutes and a TV-MA rating for mature audiences, Ruined offers a bite-sized dose of psychological thrills. While it may not cater to those seeking intricate character development, it caters to the audience's appetite for suspense and intrigue. In the realm of psychological thrillers, Ruined presents a premise that hinges on betrayal and vengeance, making it an enticing choice for fans of the genre. If you relish the tension of uncertain alliances and a plot punctuated by twists, Ruined may well pique your interest. However, for those seeking more profound character exploration, this film might leave a void to be filled elsewhere.
